                  DM Pro Help
The Command Object has 5 parts:
<command set> get (default), list, search, help, .exit.
<subsystem>  data (default), character
<datasets> combat, spell, magicitem, spelltables, thieving, savingthrow, weapons, xp , attributes
<string variable> string will be chained without quoting
<integer variable> generally a level...
<end command> .
examples:
get data attributes strength 17 .
data attributes strength 17 .
attributes strength 17 .
(all produce the same results - leveraging defaults)

search spell fire .
fire spell search .
spell search fire .
(all produce a list of spells with fire in the name)

list weapons
search weapons sword
get weapons sword, long
(examples of different level of details)

.exit. - exit
help  - show this message
